## Overview

QuakeOverlay includes 4 built-in themes for both alert and map overlays. All customization is done through the in-app Overlay Settings page. You can select a theme, then fine-tune colors, fonts, animations, and more to match your stream's look.

## Alert Themes

The alert overlay offers the following 4 themes.

### news

A banner-layout theme with a TV news broadcast style.

![News theme](/images/content/docs/theme-alert-news.svg "News alert theme")

### minimal

A card-layout theme with a simple, clean design.

![Minimal theme](/images/content/docs/theme-alert-minimal.svg "Minimal alert theme")

### impact

A banner-layout theme with a high-impact visual style.

![Impact theme](/images/content/docs/theme-alert-impact.svg "Impact alert theme")

### kawaii

A card-layout theme with a cute design.

![Kawaii theme](/images/content/docs/theme-alert-kawaii.svg "Kawaii alert theme")

## Additional Alert Themes (Sold Separately)

In addition to the built-in themes, additional themes are available for purchase. More themes are planned for the future.

### onyx

A card-layout dark and modern design theme with a two-column header and severity bar.

![Onyx theme](/images/content/docs/theme-alert-onyx.svg "Onyx alert theme")

## Alert Customization Options

After selecting a theme, you can customize the following settings.

| Setting | Default | Range / Options |
|---------|---------|-----------------|
| Position | bottom | top / bottom / center |
| Background color | theme-dependent | Color picker |
| Accent color | theme-dependent | Color picker |
| Opacity | 90 | 0–100% |
| Border color | theme-dependent | Color picker |
| Text color | theme-dependent | Color picker |
| Padding | 100% | 50–200% |
| Font size | 100% | 50–200% |
| Animation speed | 100% | 50–200% |
| Font | default | 12 fonts (see below) |
| Animation | default | default / fade / float / blur / slide / bounce |
| Animation direction | up | up / down / left / right |
| Stack method | card | banner / card / timeline / ticker / replace |
| Max display count | 2 | 1–5 |

